## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Vanilla)
- **APIs Used:**
  - [OpenWeatherMap API](https://openweathermap.org/api) â€” real-time weather data
  - [Unsplash API](https://unsplash.com/developers) â€” dynamic background images based on city
  - [GeoDB Cities API](https://rapidapi.com/wirefreethought/api/geodb-cities) â€” location autocomplete suggestions
- **Deployment:** GitHub Pages

---

## âš™ï¸ Background Image Note

If the Unsplash API fails to return a city image, a fallback background (`background.jpg`) stored locally in the project root will be used. Make sure `background.jpg` exists in the root directory to avoid blank backgrounds.

